com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.api.base
Interface AbstractTypeTopLevelScope

All Superinterfaces:
CommonTypeTopLevelScope, JSOM
All Known Subinterfaces:
ClassTopLevelScope, InterfaceTopLevelScope
public interface AbstractTypeTopLevelScope
extends CommonTypeTopLevelScope

This JSOM type supports all those things that can exist within the scope of all kinds of abstract type declarations (i.e. abstract classes or interfaces).

Author:
Dieter Habelitz

Method Detail

getMethodDeclaration

MethodDeclaration getMethodDeclaration(java.lang.String pMethodIdentifier)
Returns a certain method declaration.

Note that method definitions will be ignored by this method, i.e. only abstract methods declarations will be considered.

Parameters:
pMethodIdentifier - The identifier of the method.
Returns:
A method declaration or null if no method declaration exists for the stated identifier.

getMethodDeclarations

java.util.List<? extends MethodDeclaration> getMethodDeclarations()
Returns a list of this scope's method declarations.

Note that method definitions will be ignored by this method, i.e. only abstract methods declarations will be considered.

Calling this method equals an getMethodDeclarations(null) call.

Returns:
A list of this scope's method declarations. If there are no method declarations null will be returned.
See Also:
getMethodDeclarations(List)

getMethodDeclarations

java.util.List<MethodDeclaration> getMethodDeclarations(java.util.List<MethodDeclaration> pList)
Returns a list of this scope's method declarations.

Note that method definitions will be ignored by this method, i.e. only abstract methods declarations will be considered.

Parameters:
pList - If this argument isn't null the method declarations will be added to this list and this list object will be returned. Otherwise a new list will be created for the result.
Returns:
A list of this scope's method declarations. If there are no method declarations null will be returned, even if the argument pList isn't null.

hasMethodDeclaration

boolean hasMethodDeclaration(java.lang.String pMethodIdentifier)
Tells if this has a certain method declaration.

Note that method definitions will be ignored by this method, i.e. only abstract methods declarations will be considered.

Parameters:
pMethodIdentifier - A method identifier.
Returns:
true if a method declaration exists for the stated identifier.

hasMethodDeclaration

boolean hasMethodDeclaration()
Tells if this has at least one method declaration.

Note that method definitions will be ignored by this method, i.e. only abstract methods declarations will be considered.

Returns:
true if this has at least one method declaration.
